5:
Well, I think that's about everything I
had on my list.
11:
Not everything needs to be a
mission—we can just call that
"shopping".
15:
Affirmative!
Entering standby mode pending
further orders.
20:
Sera, I think we might have touched
on this before, but we aren't your
superiors. You needn't wait for
orders of any sort.
22:
Why don't you try doing something
that YOU want to do?
27: I… I see. In that case, pardon me.
32:
Oof, I thought we said no more of
that... nuzzling!
36:
But, Commander Light, your
instructions were to do something
that I wanted to do!
40:
Er, yes, I suppose they were. Either
way, please let me go! Eep—and
THAT part of the tail is definitely
off-limits!
45:
Affirmative!
Standing by until permission for
further nuzzling is granted.
50:
Anyway... Sera, this is your first time
in Palpebra, right? Anything catch
your attention?
66:
...Come to think of it, we're just
emptying out a room. You sure there
isn't more important work waiting
for you elsewhere?
69:
There is no point in idle chatter. Let
us complete this task without delay.
72:
Huh, Sera, take a look at this. I found
something interesting.
76:
A curious paper-based medium... Is
this a… book?
79:
That's right. There was a note inside
it too… It says… "Justice. A fitting
name for her flower."
81:
Whoever lived here was certainly an
oddball. Where did they get this
book thing from anyway?
86:
A library? I think I've heard that word
before. You're pretty knowledgeable
about this stuff, huh?
101:
M-my apologies! Were you talking
to me?
105:
Are you all right? You looked like you
were dreaming or something.
110:
There is nothing to be concerned
about! I will now proceed with town
patrol duties.
112: If you will excuse me, I must go.
122:
…A dream.
A memory? But one I do not
remember having.
124:
Is it possible that my memories were
wiped too?
126:
Why don'tcha try sayin' that to my
face again?
128:
Pfft, I don't have time for third-rate
adventurers like you who can't even
get past the Shallows.
133:
Freeze.
Unauthorized act of violence
detected.
135:
Place your hands in the air and get
down on your knees. I will hand you
over to the local authorities.
137:
My, my. No matter where you go,
you're always playing sheriff.
141:
You... You are the fugitive, Rec
Register!
148:
Hahaha! Are you talking about me?
Because I don't think I'm the only
one that's broken the rules here.
151:
Let's continue this conversation
somewhere more private. Follow me.
156:
Let's clear something up: you DO
know exactly who it was that took
out the Administrator, right?
160: I heard it all from Miss Stella.
163:
I see. But you don't have any
intention of acting on that
information—or perhaps you're at a
loss for what to do.
165:
Now that we're free of the
Administrator, I don't think there's
any need to play by someone else's
rules, if you know what I mean.
167:
What are you after here? What is
your aim?
169:
I'm just trying to get to know the
locals better, that's all.
172:
If anything I should be asking you
that. What exactly are YOU up to?
175:
You betrayed your squadron, stole
top-secret memory bytes, and
departed in such a spectacular
fashion… To what end?
176:
To play this game of pretending to
be a watchful officer of the law?
184:
Listen. If you're scheming up a
dastardly plot and need some help
getting it done—don't hesitate to
give me a call. I'll be waiting.
190:
He is correct. I can no longer act as
a guardian of the law. Not when I
abandoned my duties as
Commander.
193:
I am running away from even my
own memories.
201:
Everyone… Why have you come
here? I thought you had already
withdrawn to our HQ.
204:
You looked pretty upset earlier, you
know? We figured we should check
in on you!
208:
I… I regret that I caused you such
concern.
213:
Please, being concerned costs us
nothing. It is the very least we can
do.
216:
Should you wish to fight, or to flee,
you may do so. Whatever path you
choose, we'll walk it with you, as
comrades.
217:
You can rely on us, Sera. I don't know
how useful I will be in my current
form, but I have it on good word that
I am... soft to the touch, if that helps.
227:
This flower… Is it from the stand we
visited earlier?
230:
You seemed interested in it. I would
like you to have it.
235:
Night will fall soon. We should head
back before it grows dark.
241:
Withdrawing to primary base of
operations.
